storyContent: So, there was this old, thick forest right on the edge of town. People used to say it was haunted. Not by ghosts or anything, but by the trees themselves. They called it the Whispering Woods. If you walked through, even in the middle of the day, you could hear whispers. The creepy part? If you listened close, the whispers sounded just like someone you loved, calling for help. One brave soul went looking to see if someone was stuck there. He went in... and never came out. They say now, his voice is just another whisper in the woods.

explanation: The color palette is chosen to evoke the mysterious and eerie atmosphere of the story. #4A235A (dark purple) represents the deep, dark mystery of the forest and the unknown. #154360 (dark blue) reflects the sadness and fear associated with the haunted woods. #1ABC9C (teal) is used for moments of eerie calm and the supernatural feel of the woods. #F1C40F (yellow) symbolizes moments of tension and caution. #E74C3C (red) is used for intense moments of danger or when the story peaks in fear.
